<bioghist altrender="history" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
<head>Historical Note</head>
<p>By Special Act 474, approved June 9, 1933, the General Assembly formed the “Temporary Commission to Study the Tax Laws of the State and to Make Recommendations concerning their Revision,” which quickly took the name, “Special Tax Commission.” It consisted of seven appointed members headed by Professor Fred R. Fairchild, and a small research staff directed by Benjamin P. Whitaker. The Commission held six public hearings and obtained assistance from private citizens and state government officials. It submitted a report to Governor Wilbur Cross on November 9, 1934. The first was a 94 - page summary followed by a full report of 642 pages.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>Includes minutes, correspondence, administrative papers, papers on fiscal year change study, publicity material and a general file.</p>
</scopecontent>

